translations: n.振动器；[电子] 振子；振动按摩器；振动滚筒；簧片

phrs.translation: 混凝土振动器；混凝土路面振动整实器

sentences.sentence: They're in your dry-cleaning bags, household items and -- it turns out -- maybe even your vibrator.
sentences.translation: 它们无处不在，干洗袋或家庭物件甚至可能是在振动棒里。

sentences.sentence: In the Indiana survey, 11 percent of vibrator users reported occasional numbness and 3 percent experienced it frequently.
sentences.translation: 报告中指出有11%的使用者有麻木感，其中3%感觉频繁。

sentences.sentence: Damping rate of the vibrator of the oscillograph is one of the important parameters, as it effects the dynamic characteristics of the vibrator.
sentences.translation: 光线示波器振子的阻尼率是一个重要的特性参数，对振子的动态特性有很大影响。
